on 7/25/02 12:20 AM, minor35(-at-)juno.com at minor35(-at-)juno.com wrote:

> Easiest way to find vacuum leaks is to idle the engine at about 1200
> rpms, take a spray can of Diesel Starting fluid (Ether), spray it next to
> a vacuum connection, if the engine races that is a leak.
> The small injectors seals often get hard and leak.

My FI seals were toast but like all old parts like that, surviving by a
thread until you disturb them.  One seal just cracked in half when I touched
it.  Don't take anything apart without a new replacement handy.

